<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="597" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d597">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/250</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Cuban Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Altunaga</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-12"><hi rend="italic">January 12,
                                1928</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to refer to the note which the
                            Ambassador handed to me on December 15, 1927, containing certain
                            proposals for the modification of the commercial agreement of 1902
                            between Cuba and the United States. This matter is receiving careful
                            consideration, and I shall communicate to you the views of this
                            Government as soon as the necessary study of your Government’s proposals
                            shall have been completed.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frank B. Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>